## Add MCP Server Config (npx -y)

Allow users to run agent-recall as an MCP server without `npm install` by using `npx -y`.

### MCP Config (for Claude Desktop, Cursor, etc.)

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "agent-recall": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "agent-recall"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Claude Code one-liner

```bash
claude mcp add agent-recall -- npx -y agent-recall
```

### What's needed

- Ensure package.json has a `bin` entry pointing to the MCP server entrypoint
- Publish the package to npm
- Document the config in README.md
